Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.20,0:28:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,letting it go. And after you do that a\Nfew times, you feel freer and higher and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.20,0:29:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,better and happier, and you realize that\Nit was worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.67,0:29:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uhhuh.\N>> Okay. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.27,0:29:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N>> Hi, Dr. Hopkins. Uh, it's a privilege to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.60,0:29:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,be here and I'm very honored.\N>> Uh, my question uh this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.12,0:29:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> okay, sorry. This morning you said uh\NGod's will for us is free choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.24,0:29:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> God's will\N>> God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.60,0:29:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> for us is free choice. God's will for us\Nis free choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.12,0:29:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Free choice. Yes. Freedom is a\Nbasic spiritual reality universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.32,0:29:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Without that which there'd be no\Naccountability and there could be no
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.27,0:29:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual progression.\N>> Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.52,0:30:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. Does God have a plan for us?\N>> Does God have a plan for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.48,0:30:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It can't be answered in the way that you\Nput the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.44,0:30:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> It's a deterministic
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.48,0:30:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualization that you've given.\N>> Okay. out of the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.72,0:30:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the ultimate reality\Nemerges a creation
